description.p:
Another aspect of the present invention relates to a cable storage tray 10/110/210/310 comprising:
a body 12/212 defining a first side 14/214 and an opposing second side 16/216;
the first side 14/214 defining an inner area for storing cables;
the first side 14/214 also defining an outer area for storing cables, wherein the outer area is separated from the inner area by at least one wall 28; and
at least one magnet 18 such that the second side 14/214 of the body 12/212 is magnetically attachable to a ferromagnetic surface 54 via the at least one magnet 18.

claim.claim-text:
A cable storage tray (10/110/210/310) comprising:
a body (12/212);
a cable management structure (24, 26) positioned on the body (12/212);

characterized in that:
at least one magnet (18) is provided such that the body (12/212) is magnetically attachable to a ferromagnetic surface (54) via the at least one magnet (18).
